            "date": "2025-02-21",
            "headline": "Cryptocurrency traders face tax scrutiny. All transactions taxable, including crypto-to-crypto. Misunderstanding may lead to costly consequences.",
            "id": "035f454f-e172-49a6-80a5-51016521dfe5",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Cryptocurrency investors should be aware of increased tax scrutiny this filing season as the IRS considers all cryptocurrency transactions taxable, including those not converted to dollars. According to CoinTracker's head of tax strategy, Shehan Chandrasekera, many mistakenly believe crypto-to-crypto trades are exempt from taxes. However, under IRS rules, exchanging bitcoin for ether, for example, triggers a taxable event due to cryptocurrencies being treated as property subject to capital gains tax. It's crucial for investors to understand reporting requirements to avoid costly consequences. The article provides further details on this topic.",
            "tickers": [
                "IRS"
            ],
            "time": "02:07:31",
            "timestamp": "2025-02-21T02:07:31Z",
            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/markets/cryptocurrency/25/02/43872725/did-you-trade-crypto-this-year-3-common-tax-mistakes-that-could-cost-you-big-time-and-how-"
        },
