            "headline": "Bitcoin Breaches $98K, Ethereum, Dogecoin Flat As SEC Relaxes Crypto Enforcement: Top Analysts Are Focused On This Level For A Potential BTC Upside",
            "id": "66634ff8-03b1-48b5-9274-4bba78d16da6",
            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Top cryptocurrencies experienced mixed movement compared to sinking stock market on Thursday following news of the Securities and Exchange Commission's reduced oversight on digital assets. Bitcoin showed a gain of 1.63%, reaching $98,192.29 with an intraday high at $98,767.19 \u2014 the first time over $98,000 in a week. Ethereum rose by 0.43% to $2,734.93, peaking at $2,770.03. On the other hand, Dogecoin fell by 0.68% to $0.2536. The SEC's move to replace its crypto oversight unit with a smaller cyber fraud unit led to cryptocurrency liquidations totaling $249.79 million in 24 hours, wiping out $171 million in short positions. Notably, Bitcoin's open interest spiked by 4.25%, with more traders shorting the currency than betting on its increase, as per the Long/Short ratio.",
